{{Infobox person |name = Alessandro Longo |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1976|10|29}} |birth_place = [[Taranto]] |death_date = |death_place = |occupation = Editor in chief, technology journalist, technical evangelist }}
'''Alessandro Longo''' ([[Taranto]], 29 October 1976) is an italian [[Technology journalism|technology journalist]] and [[editor-in-chief]] of the italian newspapers Agendadigitale.eu<ref>https://www.agendadigitale.eu/about/</ref> and Forumpa.it.
He has been a regular contributor to [[La Repubblica]] (over one thousand articles published<ref>http://ricerca.repubblica.it/ricerca/repubblica?query=&fromdate=2000-01-01&todate=2016-06-11&sortby=score&author=alessandro+longo&mode=any</ref>), [[L'espresso]] and [[Il Sole 24 Ore]], since 2003.
Around one hundred of his investigative features have been published on the first pages<ref>http://rstampa.pubblica.istruzione.it/utility/imgrs.asp?numart=4VTLA7&numpag=1&tipcod=0&tipimm=1&defimm=0&tipnav=1</ref> of La Repubblica and Il Sole 24 Ore over the years.
As technical evangelist he has been hosted since 2002 in some very popular tv programs on [[Rai 1]],<ref>http://unomattinainfamiglia.blog.rai.it/2016/03/20/se-ne-parla-in-famiglia-16</ref> [[Rai 2]] and [[Rai 3]].
He is also a regular participant in the main Italian-Swiss radio station, [[Radiotelevisione svizzera]] (Radio 1).<ref>http://www.rsi.ch/rete-uno/programmi/intrattenimento/millevoci/Cyberincognite-del-terrorismo-contemporaneo-6689998.html</ref>
He wrote the first Italian book on Voice over IP technology in 2005.
